2833/**
2834 * do_sigtimedwait - wait for queued signals specified in @which
2835 * @which: queued signals to wait for
2836 * @info: if non-null, the signal's siginfo is returned here
2837 * @ts: upper bound on process time suspension
2838 */
2839static int do_sigtimedwait(const sigset_t *which, siginfo_t *info,
2840 const struct timespec *ts)
2841{
2842 ktime_t *to = NULL, timeout = KTIME_MAX;
2843 struct task_struct *tsk = current;
2844 sigset_t mask = *which;
2845 int sig, ret = 0;
2846
2847 if (ts) {
2848 if (!timespec_valid(ts))
2849 return -EINVAL;
2850 timeout = timespec_to_ktime(*ts);
2851 to = &timeout;
2852 }
2853
2854 /*
2855 * Invert the set of allowed signals to get those we want to block.
2856 */
2857 sigdelsetmask(&mask, sigmask(SIGKILL) | sigmask(SIGSTOP));
2858 signotset(&mask);
2859
2860 spin_lock_irq(&tsk->sighand->siglock);
2861 sig = dequeue_signal(tsk, &mask, info);
2862 if (!sig && timeout) {
2863 /*
2864 * None ready, temporarily unblock those we're interested
2865 * while we are sleeping in so that we'll be awakened when
2866 * they arrive. Unblocking is always fine, we can avoid
2867 * set_current_blocked().
2868 */
2869 tsk->real_blocked = tsk->blocked;
2870 sigandsets(&tsk->blocked, &tsk->blocked, &mask);
2871 recalc_sigpending();
2872 spin_unlock_irq(&tsk->sighand->siglock);
2873
2874 __set_current_state(TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE);
2875 ret = freezable_schedule_hrtimeout_range(to, tsk->timer_slack_ns,
2876 HRTIMER_MODE_REL);
2877 spin_lock_irq(&tsk->sighand->siglock);
2878 __set_task_blocked(tsk, &tsk->real_blocked);
2879 sigemptyset(&tsk->real_blocked);
2880 sig = dequeue_signal(tsk, &mask, info);
2881 }
2882 spin_unlock_irq(&tsk->sighand->siglock);
2883
2884 if (sig)
2885 return sig;
2886 return ret ? -EINTR : -EAGAIN;
2887}
2888
2889/**
2890 * sys_rt_sigtimedwait - synchronously wait for queued signals specified
2891 * in @uthese
2892 * @uthese: queued signals to wait for
2893 * @uinfo: if non-null, the signal's siginfo is returned here
2894 * @uts: upper bound on process time suspension
2895 * @sigsetsize: size of sigset_t type
2896 */
2897SYSCALL_DEFINE4(rt_sigtimedwait, const sigset_t __user *, uthese,
2898 siginfo_t __user *, uinfo, const struct timespec __user *, uts,
2899 size_t, sigsetsize)
2900{
2901 sigset_t these;
2902 struct timespec ts;
2903 siginfo_t info;
2904 int ret;
2905
2906 /* XXX: Don't preclude handling different sized sigset_t's. */
2907 if (sigsetsize != sizeof(sigset_t))
2908 return -EINVAL;
2909
2910 if (copy_from_user(&these, uthese, sizeof(these)))
2911 return -EFAULT;
2912
2913 if (uts) {
2914 if (copy_from_user(&ts, uts, sizeof(ts)))
2915 return -EFAULT;
2916 }
2917
2918 ret = do_sigtimedwait(&these, &info, uts ? &ts : NULL);
2919
2920 if (ret > 0 && uinfo) {
2921 if (copy_siginfo_to_user(uinfo, &info))
2922 ret = -EFAULT;
2923 }
2924
2925 return ret;
2926}

2963 * sys_kill - send a signal to a process

2972 info.si_errno = 0;
2973 info.si_code = SI_USER;
2974 info.si_pid = task_tgid_vnr(current);

2979
2980static int
2981do_send_specific(pid_t tgid, pid_t pid, int sig, struct siginfo *info)
2982{
2983 struct task_struct *p;
2984 int error = -ESRCH;
2985
2986 rcu_read_lock();
2987 p = find_task_by_vpid(pid);
2988 if (p && (tgid <= 0 || task_tgid_vnr(p) == tgid)) {
2989 error = check_kill_permission(sig, info, p);
2990 /*
2991 * The null signal is a permissions and process existence
2992 * probe. No signal is actually delivered.
2993 */
2994 if (!error && sig) {
2995 error = do_send_sig_info(sig, info, p, false);
2996 /*
2997 * If lock_task_sighand() failed we pretend the task
2998 * dies after receiving the signal. The window is tiny,
2999 * and the signal is private anyway.
3000 */
3001 if (unlikely(error == -ESRCH))
3002 error = 0;
3003 }
3004 }
3005 rcu_read_unlock();
3006
3007 return error;
3008}

3058static int do_rt_sigqueueinfo(pid_t pid, int sig, siginfo_t *info)
3059{

3064 (task_pid_vnr(current) != pid))

3067 info->si_signo = sig;
3068
3069 /* POSIX.1b doesn't mention process groups. */
3070 return kill_proc_info(sig, info, pid);

3146/*
3147 * For kthreads only, must not be used if cloned with CLONE_SIGHAND
3148 */
3149void kernel_sigaction(int sig, __sighandler_t action)
3150{
3151 spin_lock_irq(&current->sighand->siglock);
3152 current->sighand->action[sig - 1].sa.sa_handler = action;
3153 if (action == SIG_IGN) {
3154 sigset_t mask;
3155
3156 sigemptyset(&mask);
3157 sigaddset(&mask, sig);
3158
3159 flush_sigqueue_mask(&mask, &current->signal->shared_pending);
3160 flush_sigqueue_mask(&mask, &current->pending);
3161 recalc_sigpending();
3162 }
3163 spin_unlock_irq(&current->sighand->siglock);
3164}
3165EXPORT_SYMBOL(kernel_sigaction);
3166
3167void __weak sigaction_compat_abi(struct k_sigaction *act,
3168 struct k_sigaction *oact)
3169{
3170}
3171
3172int do_sigaction(int sig, struct k_sigaction *act, struct k_sigaction *oact)
3173{
3174 struct task_struct *p = current, *t;
3175 struct k_sigaction *k;
3176 sigset_t mask;
3177
3178 if (!valid_signal(sig) || sig < 1 || (act && sig_kernel_only(sig)))
3179 return -EINVAL;
3180
3181 k = &p->sighand->action[sig-1];
3182
3183 spin_lock_irq(&p->sighand->siglock);
3184 if (oact)
3185 *oact = *k;
3186
3187 sigaction_compat_abi(act, oact);
3188
3189 if (act) {
3190 sigdelsetmask(&act->sa.sa_mask,
3191 sigmask(SIGKILL) | sigmask(SIGSTOP));
3192 *k = *act;
3193 /*
3194 * POSIX 3.3.1.3:
3195 * "Setting a signal action to SIG_IGN for a signal that is
3196 * pending shall cause the pending signal to be discarded,
3197 * whether or not it is blocked."
3198 *
3199 * "Setting a signal action to SIG_DFL for a signal that is
3200 * pending and whose default action is to ignore the signal
3201 * (for example, SIGCHLD), shall cause the pending signal to
3202 * be discarded, whether or not it is blocked"
3203 */
3204 if (sig_handler_ignored(sig_handler(p, sig), sig)) {
3205 sigemptyset(&mask);
3206 sigaddset(&mask, sig);
3207 flush_sigqueue_mask(&mask, &p->signal->shared_pending);
3208 for_each_thread(p, t)
3209 flush_sigqueue_mask(&mask, &t->pending);
3210 }
3211 }
3212
3213 spin_unlock_irq(&p->sighand->siglock);
3214 return 0;
3215}
3216
3217static int
3218do_sigaltstack (const stack_t *ss, stack_t *oss, unsigned long sp)
3219{
3220 struct task_struct *t = current;
3221
3222 if (oss) {
3223 memset(oss, 0, sizeof(stack_t));
3224 oss->ss_sp = (void __user *) t->sas_ss_sp;
3225 oss->ss_size = t->sas_ss_size;
3226 oss->ss_flags = sas_ss_flags(sp) |
3227 (current->sas_ss_flags & SS_FLAG_BITS);
3228 }
3229
3230 if (ss) {
3231 void __user *ss_sp = ss->ss_sp;
3232 size_t ss_size = ss->ss_size;
3233 unsigned ss_flags = ss->ss_flags;
3234 int ss_mode;
3235
3236 if (unlikely(on_sig_stack(sp)))
3237 return -EPERM;
3238
3239 ss_mode = ss_flags & ~SS_FLAG_BITS;
3240 if (unlikely(ss_mode != SS_DISABLE && ss_mode != SS_ONSTACK &&
3241 ss_mode != 0))
3242 return -EINVAL;
3243
3244 if (ss_mode == SS_DISABLE) {
3245 ss_size = 0;
3246 ss_sp = NULL;
3247 } else {
3248 if (unlikely(ss_size < MINSIGSTKSZ))
3249 return -ENOMEM;
3250 }
3251
3252 t->sas_ss_sp = (unsigned long) ss_sp;
3253 t->sas_ss_size = ss_size;
3254 t->sas_ss_flags = ss_flags;
3255 }
3256 return 0;
3257}
3258
3259SYSCALL_DEFINE2(sigaltstack,const stack_t __user *,uss, stack_t __user *,uoss)
3260{
3261 stack_t new, old;
3262 int err;
3263 if (uss && copy_from_user(&new, uss, sizeof(stack_t)))
3264 return -EFAULT;
3265 err = do_sigaltstack(uss ? &new : NULL, uoss ? &old : NULL,
3266 current_user_stack_pointer());
3267 if (!err && uoss && copy_to_user(uoss, &old, sizeof(stack_t)))
3268 err = -EFAULT;
3269 return err;
3270}

3277 (void)do_sigaltstack(&new, NULL, current_user_stack_pointer());

3377/**
3378 * sys_sigprocmask - examine and change blocked signals
3379 * @how: whether to add, remove, or set signals
3380 * @nset: signals to add or remove (if non-null)
3381 * @oset: previous value of signal mask if non-null
3382 *
3383 * Some platforms have their own version with special arguments;
3384 * others support only sys_rt_sigprocmask.
3385 */
3386
3387SYSCALL_DEFINE3(sigprocmask, int, how, old_sigset_t __user *, nset,
3388 old_sigset_t __user *, oset)
3389{
3390 old_sigset_t old_set, new_set;
3391 sigset_t new_blocked;
3392
3393 old_set = current->blocked.sig[0];
3394
3395 if (nset) {
3396 if (copy_from_user(&new_set, nset, sizeof(*nset)))
3397 return -EFAULT;
3398
3399 new_blocked = current->blocked;
3400
3401 switch (how) {
3402 case SIG_BLOCK:
3403 sigaddsetmask(&new_blocked, new_set);
3404 break;
3405 case SIG_UNBLOCK:
3406 sigdelsetmask(&new_blocked, new_set);
3407 break;
3408 case SIG_SETMASK:
3409 new_blocked.sig[0] = new_set;
3410 break;
3411 default:
3412 return -EINVAL;
3413 }
3414
3415 set_current_blocked(&new_blocked);
3416 }
3417
3418 if (oset) {
3419 if (copy_to_user(oset, &old_set, sizeof(*oset)))
3420 return -EFAULT;
3421 }
3422
3423 return 0;
3424}

3428/**
3429 * sys_rt_sigaction - alter an action taken by a process
3430 * @sig: signal to be sent
3431 * @act: new sigaction
3432 * @oact: used to save the previous sigaction
3433 * @sigsetsize: size of sigset_t type
3434 */
3435SYSCALL_DEFINE4(rt_sigaction, int, sig,
3436 const struct sigaction __user *, act,
3437 struct sigaction __user *, oact,
3438 size_t, sigsetsize)
3439{
3440 struct k_sigaction new_sa, old_sa;
3441 int ret = -EINVAL;
3442
3443 /* XXX: Don't preclude handling different sized sigset_t's. */
3444 if (sigsetsize != sizeof(sigset_t))
3445 goto out;
3446
3447 if (act) {
3448 if (copy_from_user(&new_sa.sa, act, sizeof(new_sa.sa)))
3449 return -EFAULT;
3450 }
3451
3452 ret = do_sigaction(sig, act ? &new_sa : NULL, oact ? &old_sa : NULL);
3453
3454 if (!ret && oact) {
3455 if (copy_to_user(oact, &old_sa.sa, sizeof(old_sa.sa)))
3456 return -EFAULT;
3457 }
3458out:
3459 return ret;
3460}

3643static int sigsuspend(sigset_t *set)
3644{
3645 current->saved_sigmask = current->blocked;
3646 set_current_blocked(set);
3647
3648 while (!signal_pending(current)) {
3649 __set_current_state(TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE);
3650 schedule();

3656/**
3657 * sys_rt_sigsuspend - replace the signal mask for a value with the
3658 * @unewset value until a signal is received
3659 * @unewset: new signal mask value
3660 * @sigsetsize: size of sigset_t type
3661 */
3662SYSCALL_DEFINE2(rt_sigsuspend, sigset_t __user *, unewset, size_t, sigsetsize)
3663{
3664 sigset_t newset;
3665
3666 /* XXX: Don't preclude handling different sized sigset_t's. */
3667 if (sigsetsize != sizeof(sigset_t))
3668 return -EINVAL;
3669
3670 if (copy_from_user(&newset, unewset, sizeof(newset)))
3671 return -EFAULT;
3672 return sigsuspend(&newset);
3673}

3728#ifdef CONFIG_KGDB_KDB
3729#include <linux/kdb.h>
3730/*
3731 * kdb_send_sig_info - Allows kdb to send signals without exposing
3732 * signal internals. This function checks if the required locks are
3733 * available before calling the main signal code, to avoid kdb
3734 * deadlocks.
3735 */
3736void
3737kdb_send_sig_info(struct task_struct *t, struct siginfo *info)
3738{
3739 static struct task_struct *kdb_prev_t;
3740 int sig, new_t;
3741 if (!spin_trylock(&t->sighand->siglock)) {
3742 kdb_printf("Can't do kill command now.\n"
3743 "The sigmask lock is held somewhere else in "
3744 "kernel, try again later\n");
3745 return;
3746 }
3747 spin_unlock(&t->sighand->siglock);
3748 new_t = kdb_prev_t != t;
3749 kdb_prev_t = t;
3750 if (t->state != TASK_RUNNING && new_t) {
3751 kdb_printf("Process is not RUNNING, sending a signal from "
3752 "kdb risks deadlock\n"
3753 "on the run queue locks. "
3754 "The signal has _not_ been sent.\n"
3755 "Reissue the kill command if you want to risk "
3756 "the deadlock.\n");
3757 return;
3758 }
3759 sig = info->si_signo;
3760 if (send_sig_info(sig, info, t))
3761 kdb_printf("Fail to deliver Signal %d to process %d.\n",
3762 sig, t->pid);
3763 else
3764 kdb_printf("Signal %d is sent to process %d.\n", sig, t->pid);
3765}
3766#endif /* CONFIG_KGDB_KDB */
